---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import MonoRow from '../components/typography/MonoRow.astro';
import PullQuote from '../components/composition/PullQuote.astro';
import Marginalia from '../components/composition/Marginalia.astro';
import SectionRule from '../components/composition/SectionRule.astro';
import { author } from '../data/author';

const trajectory = [
  { place: 'Paris', period: '1996–2014', note: 'French-Brazilian, raised between the two.' },
  {
    place: 'Lausanne',
    period: '2014–2020',
    note: 'MSc in Robotics, EPFL. Perception, learning, control.',
  },
  {
    place: 'Amsterdam',
    period: '2020–2023',
    note: 'MIT Senseable City Lab. Urban tree morphology from LiDAR. Roboat — first engineering hire on autonomous vessels.',
  },
  {
    place: 'Rio de Janeiro',
    period: '2024–',
    note: 'MIT Senseable City Lab — founding member of the Rio branch. Favela urban science: LiDAR, CFD airflow, solar exposure, environmental risk.',
  },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="French-Brazilian researcher and builder. MIT Senseable Rio, founding member. Trained in robotics at EPFL; urban science at MIT Amsterdam; now research line on informal urban morphology in Rio."
  ogType="profile"
  register="tropical"
>
  <section class="about grid-tropical">
    <div class="col-t-1-9 about-head">
      <MonoRow pieces={['About', 'Trajectory']} />
      <h1 class="about-title">Théo Alessandro Hermann</h1>
      <p class="about-positioning">
        Researcher and builder. French-Brazilian, based in Rio. Founding member of the MIT Senseable
        City Lab — Rio branch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-t-2-8">
      <PullQuote attribution="— Thesis, locked">
        Cartesian rigor applied to tropical complexity.
      </PullQuote>
    </div>

    <div class="col-t-1-7 about-prose">
      <p>
        The work splits two ways. On one side, urban science: how the geometry of cities — formal
        and informal — produces climate, exposure, and risk at the pedestrian scale. The current
        research line at MIT Senseable Rio maps favela morphology with LiDAR and translates it into
        CFD airflow, solar exposure, and environmental signal.
      </p>
      <p>
        On the other side, robotics. Open-source benchmarks for vision-language-action models on top
        of HuggingFace lerobot. World-model work on the edge of where perception, action, and
        learning meet.
      </p>
      <p>
        The two halves talk to each other more than they look like they should. Both deal in
        geometry, measurement, and acting on the world. Both reward building the artifact before
        announcing the result.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="col-t-7-9 about-margin">
      <Marginalia voice="serif">
        Frontier methods, messy systems. The favela is not a problem to be solved — it is a system
        to be understood.
      </Marginalia>
    </aside>

    <div class="col-t-1-9">
      <SectionRule align="start">Trajectory</SectionRule>
    </div>

    <ol class="col-t-1-9 trajectory">
      {
        trajectory.map((stop) => (
          <li class="trajectory-row">
            <span class="trajectory-place">{stop.place}</span>
            <span class="trajectory-period mono-caption">{stop.period}</span>
            <span class="trajectory-note">{stop.note}</span>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>

    <div class="col-t-1-9">
      <SectionRule align="start">Credit</SectionRule>
    </div>

    <dl class="col-t-1-9 about-credit">
      <div class="credit-item">
        <dt class="mono-caption">Languages</dt>
        <dd>{author.languages.join(' · ')}</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="credit-item">
        <dt class="mono-caption">CV</dt>
        <dd><a href="/resume.pdf">Download CV (PDF)</a></dd>
      </div>
      <div class="credit-item">
        <dt class="mono-caption">Contact</dt>
        <dd><a href={`mailto:${author.email}`}>{author.email}</a></dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem) var(--space-section);
    row-gap: var(--s-8);
  }

  .about-head {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-4);
  }
  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-tropical);
    font-weight: 450;
    font-size: var(--text-display-lg);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    max-width: 20ch;
    margin: 0;
    font-variation-settings:
      'opsz' 144,
      'SOFT' 60;
  }
  .about-positioning {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 44ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-prose {
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .about-prose p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-body-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 1.25em;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .about-prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-margin {
    align-self: start;
    padding-top: var(--s-4);
  }
  @media (max-width: 719px) {
    .about-margin {
      padding-top: 0;
    }
  }

  .trajectory {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-6);
  }
  .trajectory-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 10rem 8rem 1fr;
    column-gap: var(--s-6);
    row-gap: var(--s-1);
    padding-bottom: var(--s-4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  .trajectory-place {
    font-family: var(--font-tropical);
    font-weight: 450;
    font-size: var(--text-display-sm);
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    font-variation-settings:
      'opsz' 36,
      'SOFT' 50;
  }
  .trajectory-period {
    color: var(--color-terra);
    padding-top: 0.3em;
  }
  .trajectory-note {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .trajectory-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--s-2);
      padding-bottom: var(--s-6);
    }
  }

  .about-credit {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: var(--s-8);
    padding: var(--s-4) 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .credit-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--s-2);
  }
  .credit-item dt {
    margin: 0;
  }
  .credit-item dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .credit-item dd a {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition:
      border-color 200ms ease,
      color 200ms ease;
  }
  .credit-item dd a:hover {
    color: var(--color-oxblood);
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-oxblood);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .about-credit {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--s-4);
    }
  }
</style>
